    <h3 itemprop="headline">HPE and Danfoss put excess data center heat to use</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Data centers are hot, in more ways than one. Not only are enterprises and hyperscalers building or expanding their facilities to accommodate increasing interest in artificial intelligence, but that same AI is gobbling power, and thus creating heat — a lot of it.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/06/19/hpe-and-danfoss-put-excess-data-center-heat-to-use-2/"  >(Network World)</a>
    </p>
